-- Catching typical NPC phrases
"what sell", "what buy", "list wares", "price of" -> "I don't sell anything. Just trying to have a quiet drink!", "Does I look like a damn huckster? Get rid!"
"was verkauf", "was kauf", "warenliste", "preis von" -> "Seh ich aus wie'n verdammter Hausierer? Verpiss dich!", "Ich verkauf nichts. - Will mir hier nur in Ruhe Bier rein-schütten."

-- Last catch: Think about keyphrases the player might say and that are not caught until here
"Uriel", "Urch", english -> "Hrmpf? What do you want?", "That's me. What's the matter?", "#me sighs and peeks into his beer mug."
"Uriel", "Urch" -> "Hrmpf? Was wollt Ihr?", "Das bin ich. Was ist?", "#me seufzt und wirft einen Blick in seinen Bierkrug."
"Yes" -> "I see.", "Aha?", "Sure."
"Ja" -> "Ich verstehe.", "Aha?", "Sicher."
"No" -> "Well then.", "Hrm, why?", "Ehh... waht's this about?"
"Nein" -> "Na gut.", "Hrm, warum?", "Ehh... worum geht's?"

-- Optional: Everything a player says and is not caught earlier. Response is only given 1/5 of the time
".*", english, chance(20) -> "Are you from the Serinjah folks? - You like quite strange to me...", "Damn it, I hate Greenskins!", "Leave me alone..."
".*", german, chance(20) -> "Seid ihr ein Serinjah? - Ihr seht wahrlich seltsam aus...", "Verdammt, ich hasse Grünhäute.", "Lasst mich in Frieden..."

------------------------------------------------------------------------------AC
-- Cycle Texts - Messages spoken automatically in random intervals.
-- Every NPC should contain at least 10 of those messages.
-- Emotes are possible also starting with "#me ....".

cycletext "#me gähnt ausgiebig, und lehnt sich an die Lehne seines Sessels.", "#me sits on the chair, yawning."
cycletext "#me blickt auf das Wappen an seiner Brustplatte, ein sanftes Lächeln umspielt seine Lippen für einen kruzen Moment.", "#me looks at the crest on his chest place, a soft smile playing across his lips."
cycletext "#me schüttelt den Kopf und murmelt zu sich selbst. 'Verdammte Albarianer.'", "#me sighs, muttering to himself. 'Bloody Albarians.'"
cycletext "#me kratzt sich an der Nase.", "#me scratches his nose."
cycletext "#me kratzt sich kurz zwischen den Beinen.", "#me has a quick scratch between his legs."
cycletext "#me setzt sich aufrecht hin, seine Rüstung quitsch leise, sie macht einen sperrigen Eindruck.", "#me repositions himself, his armour seeming quite heavy."
cycletext "#me blickt skeptisch auf den Boden seines Kruges und verängt die Augen zu Schlitzen.", "#me looks into his empty beer mug."
cycletext "#me starrt dich an.", "#me glares at you."
cycletext "#me pfeift ein altes Soldatenlied.", "#me whistles an old military tune."
